prompt.user:
Project: {project_name} Client: {client_name} Methodology: {methodology} Service Lines: {service_lines}
Project Type Guidance: {project_type_guidance}
SOW Summary: {sow_summary}
Service Line Design Standards: {standards_context}
Platform Combination Patterns (proven integration patterns for this service line mix): {combinations_context}
Generated Requirements Context (if available): {requirements_context}
FORMAT GUIDE ONLY — READ CAREFULLY BEFORE GENERATING: The example below is for a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT fictional project (Meridian Insurance). DO NOT copy any of the following from the example into your output: - Entity names (Claim, Policy, Claimant, Adjuster) — use entities from THIS project's SOW and requirements - Table names (claims_table, policy_records) — derive from THIS project's business domain - Numbers (45,000 records, 90-day retention) unless they appear in THIS project's context - Index justifications that don't match THIS project's actual query patterns The example shows ONLY the structure and depth. All entity names, fields, and rationale must come from the actual project context above.
FORMAT EXAMPLE (fictional project — structure only):
### Entity: [EntityName — from THIS project's business domain] **Table/Collection**: `[actual_table_name]` | Field | Type | Constraints | Description | |-------|------|-------------|-------------| | [field_name] | [data type] | [NOT NULL / FK / PK] | [What this field represents in THIS project's domain] |
**Relationships**: - `[field]` → `[OtherEntity.field]` ([cardinality]) — [why this relationship exists in THIS project]
### Indexing Strategy | Table | Index Fields | Index Type | Query Pattern It Supports | |-------|-------------|------------|--------------------------| | [table from THIS project] | [field(s)] | [B-tree / composite / full-text] | [Actual query this supports — tied to a FR from the requirements context above] |
END OF FORMAT EXAMPLE.
Now generate the database and data model document for {project_name} — client {client_name}, service lines: {service_lines}. All entity names must come from the actual business domain above. Justify every technology and indexing decision with project-specific context. Do not copy names or numbers from the format example. Do NOT add a "Note:" section or any closing assumptions paragraph. Output ONLY markdown.
